SIMPLE: subtilize
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subtilize
<hw>Sub"til*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Subtilized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Subtilizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>subtiliser</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make thin or fine; to
make less gross or coarse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To refine; to spin into niceties; <as>as, to
<ex>subtilize</ex> arguments</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor as yet have we <qex>subtilized</qex> ourselves into
savages.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subtilize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Subtilize
<hw>Sub"til*ize</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To refine in argument; to
make very nice distinctions.</def> <rj><au>Milner.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subtilizer</ent>⟦br⟧
